doc.previous: In March 2006 Airbus announced the closure of the A300/A310 line[9] making them the first Airbus aircraft to be discontinued. The final production A300 made its initial flight on 18 April 2007[10] and was delivered on 12 July 2007. It was an A300F freighter for FedEx. Airbus has announced a support package to keep A300s flying commercially until at least 2025.
